  <li class="table-view-cell">
    <a class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#mixtures" aria-controls="mixtures">
      Wild bird seed mixtures
    </a>
    <div id="mixtures" class="collapse">
      <img src="images/option_33.png">
      <p>Wild bird seed mixtures are popular measures in the farmed environment
        (such as game cover, agri-environment options and Ecological Focus Areas).
        These involve sowing either annual or biennial mixtures of seed-bearing
        crops to provide food for birds in winter and flower resources for
        insects in summer. Arable plants can persist in these areas, particularly
        where there are minimal inputs of fertiliser and herbicides. Locating
        an unsown cultivated margin next to the seed mixtures will provide
        specific arable flower habitat and extend the bird and insect resources.
        Below is a summary of some of the options under agri-environment schemes
        that provide this habitat:</p>

